data.title: Mumsnet
data.meta_description:
1. Thoughts on Daphne?
1. Daphne or Delphine?
data.text:
Maybe Daphne is due a come back at some point like other names of that era.

For me, I associate it with a chain smoking woman in her 70's/80's. I also don't like the sound- Daph, like Daffy Duck.

Not a fan at all, but if you like it, that is all that matters.

Absolutely gorgeous names, both of them.

I'd choose Daphne. I just adore it.

In reality I'd never have got either of them past DH, and we had boys anyway.

Daphne is better but not by much. I automatically think of Scooby Doo or Frasier when I hear the name.

I know two Daphnes. One in her 40s and one in her early 50s. I think there is a good reason why the name isn't heard much anymore.

Unusual. I like it.

(As a teacher, I am judgey about names. I think I‚Äôd like to have a Daphne in my class. She sounds kind and clever).

I know a toddler Daphne and have really warmed to the name, it really suits her.

I love it. I'd go for Daphne over Delphine but they're both beautiful names. Daphne is due a comeback!

I love Daphne and don‚Äôt think of Scooby Doo at all - first thought is the Malory Towers character, or was it St Clare‚Äôs? Second thought the flower

I have a little Daphne and we get compliments on her name all the time ‚ù§Ô∏è

Daphne is a very 80s name to me, in my mind I see a woman with big hair and high heels. Definitely not a baby name! Wasn't that the name of the woman in Neighbours who gave birth with her tights on? üòÇ

Delphine is very pretty, and doesn't sound anything like dolphin üôÑ

I think of Des and Daphne from Neighbours, but that probably shows I‚Äôm too old to be naming babies.

Daphne is in Bridgeton I believe, and it's increasing in popularity. It's broken the top 200 now and I think will keep rising. It fits in well with current baby names, and wouldn't be surprised if it cracks the top hundred in a couple of years. I feel I hear it all the time on name forums.
